            "content": "# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n## What This Is\n\ngit-ai is a Rust CLI that acts as a transparent git proxy to track AI-generated code authorship. It intercepts git operations, performs character-level diff analysis, and stores attribution data in Git Notes (`refs/notes/ai`) and a local SQLite database.\n\nThis is the **PageUp fork** — cloud features (API, auth, metrics) are disabled via the `cloud` cargo feature flag.\n\n## Build & Development Commands\n\nUses [Taskfile](https://taskfile.dev/) (`task <name>`) as the build runner:\n\n```bash\ntask build-debug        # Debug build (fast iteration)\ntask build              # Release build\ntask test               # Unit + integration tests (cargo test)\ntask test:e2e           # E2E tests via BATS (requires debug build)\ntask lint               # cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings\ntask format             # cargo fmt\ntask format:check       # Check formatting (CI mode)\ntask all                # Build + test + lint + doc\n```\n\nRun a single test:\n```bash\ncargo test test_name_here\ncargo test module::tests       # Run all tests in a module\ncargo test -- --nocapture      # With stdout\n```\n\nInstall locally: `task release:local` (copies to `~/.local/bin/git-ai`)\n\nCoverage: `task coverage` (requires `cargo-llvm-cov`)\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Dual-Mode Binary\n\nThe single binary dispatches based on `argv[0]` (`src/main.rs`):\n- **`git-ai`** / **`git-ai.exe`**: Routes to `commands::git_ai_handlers` — the CLI subcommands (checkpoint, stats, blame, diff, config, daemon, etc.)\n- **`git`** (proxy mode): Routes to `commands::git_handlers` — intercepts git operations, runs pre/post hooks for authorship tracking, then delegates to the real git binary\n- **Hook binary names** (legacy, sunset): Prints deprecation notice and exits\n\n### Key Modules\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `authorship/` | Core attribution engine: diff analysis (`imara-diff`), pre/post-commit processing, authorship logs, working log, rebase handling, stats |\n| `commands/` | CLI dispatch and all subcommands |\n| `commands/hooks/` | Per-git-operation hook logic (commit, rebase, merge, push, checkout, etc.) — run as part of the git proxy flow |\n| `commands/checkpoint_agent/` | Agent-specific presets for checkpoint creation (Claude, Cursor, Copilot, Windsurf, Codex, etc.) |\n| `git/` | Repository abstraction, CLI arg parsing, refs, storage, sync |\n| `daemon/` | Background async service for batching operations |\n| `mdm/` | Multi-device/model detection — agent presence detection per editor/tool |\n| `mdm/agents/` | Per-agent detection modules (claude_code, cursor, copilot, windsurf, etc.) |\n| `config.rs` | Global config singleton (`OnceLock`), loads from env vars (`envy`), git config (`gix-config`), and defaults |\n| `feature_flags.rs` | Runtime feature toggles |\n\n### Data Flow\n\n1. AI agent generates code in editor\n2. User runs `git commit` (intercepted by git-ai proxy)\n3. Pre-commit: character-level diff analysis creates attribution checkpoint (SQLite)\n4. Real git commit executes\n5. Post-commit: authorship data written as Git Note on the commit\n\n### Feature Gating\n\n```toml\n[features]\ntest-support = [\"git2\"]   # Enables git2 for integration tests\ncloud = [\"dep:keyring\"]   # Disabled in PageUp fork: api, auth, metrics, observability\n```\n\n`#[cfg(feature = \"cloud\")]` guards are throughout the codebase. Dev dependencies include `git-ai` with `test-support` enabled.\n\n## Testing\n\n| Type | Location | Runner |\n|------|----------|--------|\n| Unit | `src/**/*.rs` (`#[cfg(test)]`) | `cargo test` |\n| Integration | `tests/integration/main.rs` | `cargo test` |\n| E2E | `tests/e2e/user-scenarios.bats` | BATS |\n\nKey test crates: `insta` (snapshots), `tempfile`, `serial_test` (isolation), `rstest` (parameterized)\n\n## CI Workflows (`.github/workflows/`)\n\n- `test.yml` — main test suite\n- `lint-format.yml` — clippy + rustfmt\n- `e2e-tests.yml` — BATS end-to-end\n- `coverage.yml` — `cargo-llvm-cov` with threshold\n- `release-pageup.yml` — PageUp fork release builds\n- `sync-upstream.yml` — syncs from upstream git-ai repo\n\n## Conventions\n\n- In plan mode, always use the /ask skill so you can read the code and the original prompts that generated it. Intent will help you write a better plan\n- The binary name detection in `main.rs` is critical — changes there affect all dispatch paths\n- Config is a global singleton initialized once via `OnceLock` — not reloadable at runtime\n- Windows support is first-class: `#[cfg(windows)]` / `#[cfg(unix)]` guards throughout, named pipes on Windows vs Unix domain sockets\n",
